cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper is about a novel matching algorithm for computing dense correspondences between images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The algorithm is inspired by deep convolutional approaches, which suggests that it may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a method for estimating optical flow, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
